                        FRIEND KEYOWRD

1)Friend is keyword to function.
2)Friend function must be declared in a class and given defination outside class. 
3)Friend function can access private member outside class using object.
4)Friend function is not a member function so call it directly.
5)Static and virtual keyword never declared to friend function.



class demo
{
    private:
    int a;
    public:
    void one()
    {
        a=11;
    }
    friend void two();
};
void two()
{
    demo x;
    x.a=16;
}
void three()
{
    demo y;
    y.a=27;
}
int main()
{
    demo p;
    p.one();
    two();
    three();
    return 0;
}